-- De Beers’s $295 Million Antitrust Settlement Affirmed by Court
-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 2011-12-21T11:07:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/de-beers-s-295-million-antitrust-settlement-affirmed-by-court.html
The  U.S. Court of Appeals  affirmed
approval of a settlement by  De Beers  of a class action lawsuit
through a payment of $295 million to U.S. jewelry makers,
retailers and consumers who made purchases from 1994.  The judgment was made yesterday in the third circuit,
according to a Dec. 20 entry on the court’s docket.  The case is Arrigotti Fine Jewelry v. De Beers SA, 08-
02881, U.S. Court of Appeals, Third Circuit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  